text.section:
On or before the first Monday of June and December of each year, the clerk of a circuit court shall return to the Comptroller, under oath, an account of the licenses issued by the clerk, which states:
The number of licenses issued of each grade and kind;
The date each license was issued;
The amount of money received for each license;
The person to whom each license was issued; and
The number, grade, and description of all blank licenses remaining.
